    Validate a wearable-anomaly time series object

    validate_ts.Rd

    Validate a wearable-anomaly time series object

    validate_ts(x, lower = attr(x, "lower"), upper = attr(x, "upper"))

has_issues(issues)

    Arguments

    x

    A wa_ts object created by as_wearable_ts().

    lower, upper

    Numeric bounds used to flag out-of-range values. Defaults to the attributes stored on x.

    issues

    Output tibble returned by validate_ts().

    Value

    A tibble recording detected issues with columns issue, id, time, value, and details. A zero-row tibble is returned when no issues are found.

    Examples

    data <- toy_cgm(n_id = 1, n = 6)
ts <- as_wearable_ts(data, id = id, time = time, value = value)
validate_ts(ts)
#> # A tibble: 0 × 5
#> # ℹ 5 variables: issue <chr>, id <chr>, time <dttm>, value <dbl>, details <chr>
